Communication between users and service providers

A service may be automatically decided by the system that it needs approval at upload time. An administrator downloads the service file, inspects it and decides if it needs further testing. If so, he does it or delegates it to appropriate people, and after the checking is done, then the Administrator approves it and makes it usable by the end users, or disapproves it with specifying a reason, which is sent to the service provider or the developer who uploaded the service.
All involved people (that uploaded the service or configured to be notified) will receive a notification about the feedback
Developer or Service provider may re-request approval for a service that has been disapproved, after they have fixed the problems.
Any role can provide feedback on every service: review, rating & ranking, question/answer, bug, satisfaction, proposal of new feature etc.
